For months, the government-controlled media has launched an alarming all-out offensive against Ankara.
Suddenly, it seemed that the Turks were responsible for everything.
Among them, the most serious are the accusations from high-ranking officials: Mr. Erdogan's family profited from illegal oil transactions in the so-called Islamic State-controlled areas of Syria.
He has categorically denied that claim.
However, news from St. Petersburg suggests that it's time to look forward.
After all, the meeting was premised on Putin receiving an apology from Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
Russia can declare victory.
