First, Erdogan was almost ousted after a failed coup last month, so he needs the support of all his friends.
It is clear that the constant terrorist attacks have taken a heavy toll on him.
At the same time, there are also economic incentives.
Russian sanctions have hit Turkey hard, particularly by banning charter flights that transport millions of Russian tourists to Turkish shores every year.
That number has fallen by nearly 90 percent.
With flights resumed, Russian travel agencies and charter companies will be relieved.
They will be on the eve of the end of the season with a wave of Mediterranean tourism.
