Xiamen girl Zhang Binbin: "beautiful hands" started the road to shooting, and her career has been "reversed" several times
Zhang Donghong of Dongyuan Village, Xiang'an District, Xiamen, just replaced the 29-inch old TV at home with a 65-inch large TV a few days ago.
The daughter of this ordinary farmer is Zhang Binbin, who won the silver medal in the women's 50-meter rifle three-position final at the Rio Olympics for China on the evening of the 11th.
On the night of the 11th, in front of this new TV, Zhang Donghong and his wife and dozens of relatives and friends witnessed the magical process of their daughter catching up all the way, from being eliminated in the almost preliminary round to almost reversing.
In the competition of the day, Zhang Binbin once ranked in the middle and lower reaches, and it seemed that he was very far away from the final.
But his parents, relatives and friends did not give up, and kept scrolling through the text live broadcast, seeing that as the other players finished the race, Zhang Binbin's ranking improved all the way, and finally locked the final seat, and his family suddenly erupted in cheers.
In the final, Zhang Binbin was once ranked low, and the last few shots became more and more stable, and he only won the silver medal by 0.2 rings behind the champion.
Zhang Binbin, who is 27 years old this year, has almost missed this hard-won silver medal several times in his 16-year shooting career.
His mother, Zhang Xiaolong, told reporters that when they hesitated, Zhang Binbin found several "novelists" from the same village.
These "novelists" were children from the same village who were recommended to participate in the training camp at the same time, including Zhang Binbin's cousin.
Not long after entering the Xiamen team, Zhang Binbin once again took the initiative to return to Xiang'an's school because of family difficulties and other reasons.
But after his enlightenment coach Zhang Yajie repeatedly did his work, Zhang Binbin returned to the Xiamen team.
After entering the provincial team, Zhang Binbin once returned home again because he couldn't enter the national team because he couldn't get into the national team.
This time, not only Coach Zhang Yajie, but also the leaders and coaches of the Xiamen Shooting and Archery Sports Center and the Fujian Provincial Team came to the house and finally persuaded Zhang Binbin to return to the provincial team.
Just like yesterday's game, this Xiamen girl's persistence achieved one reversal after another on the road of shooting.
"Each coach has a different way of selecting players, and when I saw that Binbin's hands were beautiful, I immediately fell in love. ”
Zhang Donghong also recalled that in the training test, although her daughter's results were not the best, the number of rings played was very stable, which was also an important reason why Zhang Binbin attracted coaches.
In the process of training Zhang Binbin, what impressed Zhang Yajie the most was the input of this peasant girl.
He recalled that more than a year after Zhang Binbin joined the Xiamen shooting team, the team conducted a long-term training in vertical shooting, and required the team members to not move for half an hour.
Zhang Xiaolong told reporters that his daughter has always been a quiet and well-behaved child, and she likes to draw and make handmade toys since she was a child.
"Originally, I would make clothes and sew and mend at home, and Binbin would pick up some leftovers and make dolls by himself. ”
She said that her daughter often sews handmade toys by herself, and she is good at drawing, from the facial features of the dolls to the clothing, she can always make them lifelike.
As an athlete, Zhang Binbin and his family get together less and leave more, and can only go home on holidays, and usually rely on phone calls.
Parents said that whether it was meeting or calling, Zhang Binbin rarely talked about his hard work, and more talked about happy things with his parents.
I usually don't see my daughter, and my parents carefully store their daughter's paintings when she was a child and the honors of the past years at home.
Zhang Xiaolong showed his daughter's cartoons to reporters, "If she hadn't been a shooter, she would have continued to draw."
In the living room on the second floor of Zhang Binbin's house, there is a cabinet full of medals, medals and certificates she has received.
Zhang Donghong placed the medals and medals neatly, and the certificates were put into a folder for preservation, "These are the honors that Binbin has worked hard for more than ten years, and we all cherish them." ”
