On the morning of August 12, the Information Office of the State Council held a press conference on the operation of the national economy in July 2016.
Sheng Laiyun, spokesman of the National Bureau of Statistics and director of the Department of Comprehensive Statistics of the National Economy, said that in July, the growth rate of some indicators of the national economy slowed down, but it still operated within a reasonable range.
According to the data released by the National Bureau of Statistics, the growth rate of fixed asset investment and total imports fell in July.
Sheng Laiyun said: With regard to the operation of the national economy in July, I would like to borrow a phrase once said by the premier: "There are fluctuations, but the trend is still improving," which can better summarize the characteristics of the economic operation in July.
He explained that "there are fluctuations" means that the growth rate of some economic indicators did fall in July.
Because the domestic and foreign economies are still in deep adjustment in July, the international situation is complex and changeable, and the recovery of the world economy is less than expected, so the export pressure is still relatively large.
Judging from the domestic situation, the entire economy is still in the critical stage of adjustment, the pain of adjustment is being released, and the economy is facing considerable downward pressure, so some indicators are somewhat fluctuating.
Sheng Laiyun pointed out that there is a special situation in July, the flood disaster is more serious, and the high temperature and hot weather have brought some impact on the production and operation of some areas.
According to the latest information released by the Ministry of Civil Affairs, more than 60 million people across the country have been affected by the disaster, and the direct economic loss has exceeded 200 billion yuan.
From the perspective of industry, investment, and transportation-related indicators, these areas are affected to varying degrees.
The growth rate of weekly cargo transshipment volume in July fell by 3.6 percentage points from the previous month, and the flood disaster had a certain impact on traffic in these areas.
Judging from these factors, it is normal for some indicators to fluctuate in July, and it is also expected.
He said that "the trend is still improving" refers to the fact that although the economic growth rate has declined, the overall economic operation is stable, and the general trend of steady progress and steady improvement has not changed.
CPI rose 1.8% in July, up 0.2% month-on-month; The CPI rose by 2.1% from January to July, so the price situation is generally stable.
According to the statistics of the Chongqing Meteorological Bureau's portal on the high temperature weather in various districts and counties, except for Youyang, the rest of the city can receive different degrees of high temperature allowances.
At present, at least 28 provinces in the country have clarified the standards for the payment of allowances, but the standards for the issuance of subsidies are not the same in each province and city, while Chongqing receives the high temperature allowance in the form of a high temperature working day allowance.
Those above 35°C and below 37°C will be issued at the standard of not less than 10 yuan per person per day, and those above 37°C will be issued at the standard of not less than 15 yuan per person per day.
Employees with high temperature above 40 °C can receive a monthly allowance of up to 20 yuan/day (except for those who have already enjoyed the allowance for high-temperature work in accordance with the law).
According to this standard, Kaizhou, which had the most days of hot weather last month, could receive 330 yuan, and Chengkou, which had the fewest days, received 80 yuan, while Youyang's highest temperature did not meet the high temperature standard, so there was no high temperature allowance.
In the past, many units would use soft drinks to offset the high temperature allowance, but the Municipal Work Safety Supervision Bureau said that this practice was not in line with the current measures.
If the employee stops working or shortens the working hours due to hot weather, the employer shall not deduct or reduce the employee's wages.
According to the Municipal Bureau of Human Resources and Social Security, employees who encounter high temperature work but do not receive high temperature allowance can fight for their legitimate rights and interests through the labor dispute mediation agency where the enterprise is located, or call 12333 to complain.
If an employer refuses to pay the high temperature allowance, the worker may file a complaint with the competent department of human resources and social security at or above the county level where the employer is employed.
At the same time, since the high temperature allowance is a part of the salary, not a welfare, it should be included in the total salary and the individual income tax should be deducted.
Therefore, the high temperature allowance is not within the minimum wage and must be paid in cash and cannot be replaced by in-kind beverages or other goods.
