On some nights, the ionosphere is filled with free electrons, which means that radio signals can travel farther.
According to a report on the website of the monthly magazine Popular Science on August 11, the US Air Force is interested in replicating this effect.
While the ionosphere, with its stable abundance of free electrons, could help people listen to a university radio station at the edge of its range, it may not be of interest to the U.S. Air Force.
The electron-laden ionosphere means that the radio used by the military has a greater range and may provide some protection for Global Positioning System (GPS) signals from solar storms.
The ultimate goal may be to build a series of CubeSats on demand that can strengthen the ionosphere when needed.
But first, the teams contracted by the Air Force must prove that the science works.
Industry data show that in 2015, the total scale of coal production capacity was close to 6 billion tons, and the national coal overcapacity was 1.8 billion tons.
In the past ten years, the State Council has issued a total of five notices to eliminate excess and backward production capacity.
Although the first four were not targeted at the coal industry, the target industry was directly related to the coal industry.
From November last year to January this year, the price of 5,500 kcal thermal coal in Qinhuangdao hovered at a low level of 370 yuan/ton for a long time, and 90% of coal companies fell into losses.
Since February, coal prices have gradually rebounded, and recently the price of thermal coal in Qinhuangdao has risen for four consecutive weeks, rising to a 16-month high, once climbing to 436 yuan per ton, up nearly 70 yuan from the beginning of the year.
As prices rise, worries arise: Will a number of small coal mines resume work and production?
In this regard, Kuang Xianming, director of the Economic Institute of China (Hainan) Reform and Development Research Institute, analyzed and interpreted.
Kuang Xianming: The reduction of production capacity has attracted great attention from all parties, and the report card of the coal industry's capacity reduction announced today does make everyone feel more worried.
These three superficial factors still reflect the reason why the transformation of our growth mode has lagged behind in the past, that is, the government-led growth mode has not yet been fundamentally changed.
Second, this is also directly related to the promotion of local governments, in the process of capacity reduction, funds and corresponding supporting measures must be in place, from this point of view, the difference between different regions is indeed relatively large.
Third, if some provinces that are currently making slower progress want to catch up in the second half of the year, they may face greater risks.
In this case, relying on central incentives and subsidies to promote the process of capacity reduction may have a certain negative impact.
First of all, de-capacity is not simply a matter of total control.
Our aim is to eliminate outdated production capacity, promote structural optimization, and reconstruct the new business format of the entire coal industry.
In the process of deploying capacity reduction, local governments must combine capacity reduction with the transformation and upgrading of the coal industry, and vigorously develop related service industries.
Second, if we want to complete this year's task of reducing production capacity within this year, we still have to give full play to the power of administrative supervision and administrative supervision.
Finally, we need to strengthen the role of social security as a backstop.
Because the market is directly related to the issue of employment, we must strengthen the employment skills training for employees and workers.
