Newcomers who have just joined the company love to communicate with their colleagues online, "because they are not familiar with each other when they have just joined the unit, and through the likes and comments on social platforms, the relationship is much closer than before."
People who love to make friends also often communicate online, "I haven't been in touch with my friends for a while because of some misunderstandings, and then I have a few conversations in a large group before I get warm up again." ”
IT engineer Wu Yan is a deep network social enthusiast, most of his social life takes place online, and the number of online contacts is several times that of offline circle of friends.
Wu Yan himself admitted that he is more "like a fish in water" on the Internet.
"You can reply to your friends when it's convenient for you, because there is a lot of time to think about the words and the words can be expressed more clearly. ”
"The comings and goings hidden under the ID avoid face-to-face interpersonal collisions, not only have room for maneuver, but even give each other more time and space to think about words and deeds. ”
"People of different identities have the same right and efficiency to speak, and all kinds of social concerns in real life seem to be eliminated in cyberspace. ”
