If the number of fraudulent text messages sent in a group reaches a certain amount, even if the fraud is not successful, the crime of fraud can be punished.
The Wolong District People's Court of Nanyang City, Henan Province investigated and found that from September 30 to October 4, 2015, the defendant Li Huiwang successively used fake base station equipment to send fraudulent information in Tongbai County and Nanyang Urban District.
In the same year, at about 10 o'clock on October 5, when the defendant came to a hotel room in Wolong District, Nanyang City, again to use a fake base station to send fraudulent text messages, he was arrested by the public security police.
After evaluation, the pseudo base station equipment sent 62,228 text messages on October 4, 2015, causing an average communication interruption of more than 8 seconds to less than 10 minutes for 62,228 mobile phone users.
After trial, the court held that the defendant Li Huiwang used fake base stations to send a total of 62,228 fraudulent text messages to an unspecified number of people, and his behavior constituted the crime of fraud.
With regard to the defender's suggestion that the defendant was an attempted offender when he was arrested and did not cause consequences, and that he had a good attitude of admitting guilt, it is recommended that his opinion on a lighter punishment be adopted.
Based on the nature of the defendant's crime, his attitude in admitting guilt, and other circumstances, he was sentenced to 4 years and 6 months imprisonment and fined 10,000 yuan for the crime of fraud.
