Bulgaria saw inflation for the first time in eight months
National statistics show that the monthly inflation rate in Bulgaria in July was 1%.
This is the highest inflation rate in several years (since June 2012). Inflation crossed zero for the first time since October last year (0.2%).
The average annual inflation rate (as measured by the consumer price index) over the past 12 months (August 2015 to July 2016) was -0.8% compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014 to July 2015).
The consumer price index for July 2016 was 101.0% compared to June 2016, and the monthly inflation rate was 1.0%.
Year-to-date inflation (July 2016 vs. December 2015) is -0.2%. The annual inflation rate in July 2016 was -0.2% compared to July 2015.
Compared to the previous month, prices of the following categories of consumer goods increased in July 2016: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7%), transportation (1.8%), entertainment and culture (6.3%), restaurants and hotels (1.2%), and other goods and services (0.3%).
Prices decreased in clothing and footwear (2.2%), furniture, appliances and routine maintenance (0.5%), and medical (0.1%).
Prices were the same as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco, housing, water, electricity, gas and other fuels, communications, and education.
