Staying up late to watch the Olympics is easy to damage the heart
The Brazilian Olympics are in full swing, and even if the event is broadcast in the middle of the night in China, many citizens will stay up late to watch it.
In this regard, the doctor specially reminded that staying up late to watch the event has health risks and may cause cardiovascular disease.
If you stay up late for a long time, the hormone will still be secreted in large quantities, and the human body will continue to be in a state of tension and excitement, unable to recover normally, which is easy to cause vasoconstriction and increased blood pressure, thereby causing cardiovascular diseases.
Han Zhiyuan especially reminded that groups with cardiovascular risk factors such as hypertension, high blood sugar, high blood lipids, smoking habits, and family history will be more likely to cause cardiovascular disease if they stay up late.
If you stay up late for a long time, not only cardiovascular function will be affected, but also gastrointestinal function, immune system, neuroendocrine system will be affected, and even the risk of cancer will increase.
For elderly friends, Han Zhiyuan suggested that try not to stay up late to watch the Olympic games, especially those with a history of cardiovascular disease.
During the last "World Cup" football match, Han Zhiyuan once treated a patient in his 60s, whose myocardial infarction may be related to staying up late to watch the game.
Han Zhiyuan introduced that since the beginning of this year, his department has received some patients with myocardial infarction or stroke around the age of 25, which is largely caused by the patient's long-term stay up late lifestyle.
1. Don't stay up late every day, occasionally stay up late to watch your favorite sports, and wait for the next day to watch the replay of other sports.
2. Replenish water in a timely manner when staying up late and eat more fruits can prevent blood vessel blockage and enhance the body's immunity.
