The head of the Industrial Coordination Department of the National Development and Reform Commission pointed out here today that steel overcapacity is a global problem.
In recent years, China's capacity utilization rate has been higher than the global average, and also higher than that of the United States, Europe and other countries and regions.
China has taken resolute and effective measures to resolve excess capacity, and the results are gradually emerging.
The person in charge pointed out that the Party Central Committee and the State Council attach great importance to the global problem of steel overcapacity.
All departments and regions will actively implement the deployment of the State Council, carry out work conscientiously, and reduce crude steel production capacity by about 45 million tons this year.
Starting from China's national conditions, China does not encourage steel exports, on the contrary, it has also taken a series of practical measures to control steel exports.
The person in charge stressed that the international trade of steel products is essentially a market behavior, which is derived from the demand of importing countries, consumers after comprehensive consideration of product cost performance and other factors.
The implementation of trade protection measures will not help fundamentally solve the development problem of the global steel industry, on the contrary, it will only cause further impact on the international trade order.
When talking about debt, the person in charge stressed that resolving the debt problem is an important issue that needs to be properly handled in the process of resolving excess capacity.
Due to the large scale and wide range of assets of iron and steel enterprises, the debt relationship of some enterprises is complex, and if it is not properly disposed of, it may cause regional risks.
According to the person in charge, in recent years, with the increasing downward pressure on the economy, the total social demand has gradually weakened, the capacity utilization rate of some industries has declined, and the production and operation difficulties of enterprises have increased.
Some enterprises do not adapt to the changes in the market environment, and their production and operation are difficult to continue or even on the verge of bankruptcy, but they are restricted by some institutional and institutional factors, and there are many obstacles to exit in a market-oriented way, becoming "zombie enterprises".
The existence of such enterprises distorts market signals, reduces the efficiency of factor resource utilization, increases social management costs, and hinders the establishment of a fair competition market environment.
The main reasons for the loss are the same as the difficulties faced by the global steel industry – sluggish market demand and low capacity utilization.
China mainly adopts market mechanisms, economic means, and rule of law methods, and the government mainly does a good job in ensuring the work of ensuring a fair and just market order.
The person in charge stressed that in the next step, we must unswervingly continue to do a good job in reducing production capacity and ensure the completion of the target task of resolving crude steel production capacity of 100 million ~ 150 million tons in five years.
